1 under the contract up to the amount of the appropriation made for the award and
2 execution of the contract, including any authorized change orders, together with
3 attorney fees and interest as provided for by this Section. If the public entity
4 prevails in an action brought against it pursuant to this Subsection, the
5 contractor shall be liable for reasonable attorney fees. Any claim by a public
6 entity to recover liquidated damages pursuant to Subsection C of this Section
7 shall not be subject to the mandamus proceeding.
8 EF. A declaration that a public works contract is null and void as being
9 contrary to the provisions of R.S. 38:2211 et seq. shall not affect amounts due and
10 payable under the contract, including overhead and profit, for the work performed
11 by or on behalf of the contractor.
12 Section 2. This Act shall become effective upon signature of the governor or, if not
13 signed by the governor, upon expiration of the time for bills to become law without signature
14 by the governor, as provided in Article III, Section 18 of the Constitution of Louisiana. If
15 vetoed by the governor and subsequently approved by the legislature, this Act shall become
16 effective on the day following such approval.
